race.comment: OPTIMALITY (4) got around 352m in a swift 19.70 when winning a Grade 5 at this track last start. In winning form and can measure up again. OUT OF AUSTRIAN (3) started big odds last time but hit the ground running with a strong early split, giving a sight but fading only late to finish second (19.78) at this track over 352m. Must be included in calculations. FARMOR LEFT (1) struggled to get involved last start after missing the jump at this track, but prior to that won by 2.75 lengths at this track (19.65) beating Coalman Jack in a Mix 5 on October 22. Solid formlines coming through his last run. One of the better hopes. VIENNA ON CALL (7) did a good job to finish second last time out over 352m at this track (19.88) in a Grade 4, the second top-three finish on the trot.
